.br
\fP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
Da \fIpthread_condattr_getclock\fP() function shall obtain tha value
of tha \fIclock\fP attribute from tha attributes object
referenced by \fIattr\fP. Da \fIpthread_condattr_setclock\fP() function
shall set tha \fIclock\fP attribute up in a initialized
attributes object referenced by \fIattr\fP. If \fIpthread_condattr_setclock\fP()
is called wit a \fIclock_id\fP argument that
refers ta a CPU-time clock, tha call shall fail.
.LP
Da \fIclock\fP attribute is tha clock ID of tha clock dat shall
be used ta measure tha timeout steez of \fIpthread_cond_timedwait\fP().
Da default value of tha \fIclock\fP attribute
shall refer ta tha system clock.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.LP
If successful, tha \fIpthread_condattr_getclock\fP() function shall
return zero n' store tha value of tha clock attribute of
\fIattr\fP tha fuck into tha object referenced by tha \fIclock_id\fP argument.
Otherwise, a error number shall be moonwalked back ta indicate
the error.
.LP
If successful, tha \fIpthread_condattr_setclock\fP() function shall
return zero; otherwise, a error number shall be returned
to indicate tha error.
.SH ERRORS
.LP
These functions may fail if:
.TP 7
.B EINVAL
Da value specified by \fIattr\fP is invalid.
.sp
.LP
Da \fIpthread_condattr_setclock\fP() function may fail if:
.TP 7
.B EINVAL
Da value specified by \fIclock_id\fP do not refer ta a known clock,
or be a CPU-time clock.
.sp
.LP
These functions shall not return a error code of [EINTR].
